CyberPup Privacy Policy
Last Updated: September 2025
1. INTRODUCTION
CyberPup ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy and maintaining the highest standards of data protection. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our cybersecurity education mobile application ("App").
By using our App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our App.
2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
2.1 Information You Voluntarily Provide
    ‚Ä¢ Email Addresses (Optional): When you use our breach checking feature, you may voluntarily enter your email address to check if it has been involved in known data breaches. This feature is entirely optional and user-initiated.
    ‚Ä¢ Device Information (Optional): You may voluntarily provide information about your devices (type, operating system, model) to receive personalized security recommendations.
2.2 Information We Do NOT Collect
We do not collect, store, or process the following:
    ‚Ä¢ Personal identification information beyond what you voluntarily provide
    ‚Ä¢ Location data or GPS coordinates
    ‚Ä¢ Contact lists, photos, or personal files
    ‚Ä¢ Browsing history or web activity outside the App
    ‚Ä¢ Biometric data
    ‚Ä¢ Financial or payment details
    ‚Ä¢ Social media accounts or profiles
    ‚Ä¢ Device identifiers for tracking
2.3 Local Data Storage
We store the following only on your device:
    ‚Ä¢ Lesson and progress data
    ‚Ä¢ Completed security checks and validation results
    ‚Ä¢ Achievements, badges, and gamification progress
    ‚Ä¢ App preferences and settings
    ‚Ä¢ Device audit results and recommendations
    ‚Ä¢ Streak tracking
This data is stored locally using React Native AsyncStorage. While AsyncStorage is not encrypted by default, no sensitive data (such as passwords, financial info, or personal identifiers) is stored. All data is cleared when you uninstall the App.
3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
3.1 Breach Checking Feature
    ‚Ä¢ Your email address is sent to XposedOrNot.com, a third-party security service.
    ‚Ä¢ The service checks your email against known breach databases.
    ‚Ä¢ Neither our App nor XposedOrNot permanently stores your email.
    ‚Ä¢ This feature is optional and requires your explicit action.
3.2 Educational Content and Progress Tracking
Locally stored data is used to:
    ‚Ä¢ Track your learning progress
    ‚Ä¢ Provide personalized recommendations
    ‚Ä¢ Display achievements and streaks
    ‚Ä¢ Save preferences and settings
3.3 Security Alerts and Updates
The App may fetch general cybersecurity news and alerts from public RSS feeds. No personal data is involved in this process.
4. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
4.1 XposedOrNot API
    ‚Ä¢ Provider: XposedOrNot.com
    ‚Ä¢ Purpose: Check email addresses against known breaches
    ‚Ä¢ Data Shared: Only the email you enter
    ‚Ä¢ Retention: Email addresses are not stored
    ‚Ä¢ Security: All communication uses HTTPS
4.2 RSS-to-JSON Services
    ‚Ä¢ Used to fetch cybersecurity news and alerts
    ‚Ä¢ No personal information is shared
4.3 Analytics Services (Optional)
We use PostHog, a privacy-focused analytics platform, only with your explicit consent:
    ‚Ä¢ What we collect: Anonymous usage patterns, feature interactions, and app performance data
    ‚Ä¢ What we DON'T collect: Personal information, device data you enter, or any sensitive security information
    ‚Ä¢ Purpose: To improve the app and create better cybersecurity experiences
    ‚Ä¢ Your control: You can opt out at any time in Settings
    ‚Ä¢ Data handling: All data is anonymized and encrypted, no personal identifiers are used
    ‚Ä¢ Third-party: PostHog processes data according to their privacy policy at posthog.com/privacy
We do not use:
    ‚Ä¢ Advertising networks or tracking for marketing purposes
    ‚Ä¢ Social media tracking pixels
    ‚Ä¢ Cross-app tracking or data brokers
5. DATA SECURITY
We implement safeguards to protect your information:
5.1 Technical Safeguards
    ‚Ä¢ All data transmission uses HTTPS (TLS 1.2+)
    ‚Ä¢ No sensitive data stored locally
    ‚Ä¢ Local data stored only on your device via AsyncStorage
    ‚Ä¢ Input validation and sanitization for all user inputs
    ‚Ä¢ Rate limiting on API calls
5.2 Operational Safeguards
    ‚Ä¢ No external servers or databases
    ‚Ä¢ No user accounts or authentication systems
    ‚Ä¢ No third-party data sharing beyond breach checking
    ‚Ä¢ Regular code reviews and privacy-first development
6. YOUR RIGHTS AND CHOICES
    ‚Ä¢ Opt-Out: You can choose not to use the breach checking feature.
    ‚Ä¢ Data Deletion: All data can be removed by uninstalling the App.
    ‚Ä¢ Progress Control: Reset or export your progress at any time within the App.
    ‚Ä¢ No Marketing: We do not send promotional emails or notifications.
7. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
Our App is educational and may be used by all ages. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal information, please contact us.
For users under 18, we recommend parental supervision when using the breach checking feature.
8. INTERNATIONAL USERS
This Privacy Policy applies worldwide. Depending on your location, local privacy rights (such as GDPR in the EU or CCPA in California) may apply. CyberPup does not sell personal data and relies on your consent for optional features such as breach checking.
9. DATA RETENTION
    ‚Ä¢ Local Data: Retained until you delete the App or reset your progress.
    ‚Ä¢ Third-Party Data: Email addresses are not retained by CyberPup or XposedOrNot. Breach results are not stored. RSS feed data may be cached temporarily.
10. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in practices or laws. Updates will be shown in the App with an updated "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of the App means you accept the updated Privacy Policy.
